Text.Value: But you are stronger than the hunger. You can resist, you will resist. I'm sure of it.
Then again, we're talking about tadpoles inserted into our brains by rubber-skinned tentacle monsters. There's nothing usual about it.
I am born of the Lord of Murder. I am a Bhaalspawn.
Listen to me. I knew another like you - Gorion's Ward, one of Baldur's Gate's great heroes. Bhaal's blood ran through their veins too.
I am death, I am murder. I am the Chosen of Bhaal!
I've got no memory of my past. Could the parasite have done that?
Is that so? Maybe that's fear of false accusation I hear in your voice. Or maybe it's guilt.
Anger, I understand. We've been preyed on by illithids, suffered insertion of a mind-bending worm.
Isobel is no more. Glory to the darkness left in her absence!
All right.
They burned away their own darkness with their own inner light. They chose courage, they chose honour - and so can you.
It's the pride you take in it, as if you've done all sixteen planes a great favour.
Gods - you left Last Light for the shadows to feed on. You should be shamed for your villainy, not extolled for it.
You don't.
All the more reason to stick close, I think you'll agree.
I want to talk about what happened. About your... affliction.
Bloodthirst is another matter. But perhaps not too big of one, if it's a devil or demon's flesh you're wanting to tear.
I could have killed you when I was possessed. How do I know I won't try again?
I didn't kill Alfira, I swear it.
Whichever is true, I will not stand for more innocent blood being shed in our camp.
By the gone gods. It isn't the blood you've spilled or the lives you've snuffed out that horrify me most.
Hells - it explains so much.
Bow before me, for I have become the Slayer!
I'm so glad to hear it. If I had a bottle of Dragondew, I'd open it in your honour.
Hells. Is this really what you've become - the kind of monster I once vowed to slay?
Don't bother answering - I already know.
I've got this... bloodthirst. An urge to destroy, maim, kill.
When the Absolute falls, I wager our alliance falls with it.
I have conquered my urges. The bloodlust has faded.
I was hoping you would. It's been on my mind.
Let's change the subject.
Seems unusual to me.
